\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 72. V. dubyana} Burnat ex Gremli,{\i  Neue Beitr. Fl. Schweiz}{\b  5}: 15 (1890). Glabrous or shortly hairy perennial, without leafy stolons. Stems 10-30 cm; upper internodes short. Lower leaves 2-4 cm, orbicular, the upper narrowly lanceolate or linear. Stipules digitately divided to the base; segments linear, 4-6 on the outer and 2-3 on the inner side, the terminal scarcely wider. Flowers 2-2·5 cm, violet; lower petal with a yellow spot. Spur 5-6 mm, curved downwards, slender, much longer than calycine appendages. 2n = 20.{\i  Dry pastures and rocky places; calcicole. • Italian Alps, between} 7° 30' {\i and }11° {\i E}. It.
\par

