\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 74. V. lutea} Hudson, {\i Fl. Angl. }331 (1762). Perennial, with a slender, branching rhizome and without leafy stolons. Stems 10-20(-40) cm, usually simple, glabrous. Leaves ovate, oblong or lanceolate, glabrous or pubescent. Stipules palmately or pinnately divided into 3-5 segments, sometimes pubescent on the margins and the veins. Peduncles usually c. 6 cm. Flowers 1·5-3 cm, yellow, violet or parti-coloured; lower petal with a dense network of veins. Spur 3-6 mm, short, slender, twice as long as calycine appendages, or sometimes scarcely longer. {\i W. & C. Europe, southwards to the Pyrenees.} Au Be Br Cz Ga Ge Hb He Ho Hs Po.
\par

