\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 76. V. hispida} Lam.,{\i  Fl. Fr. }{\b 2}: 679 (1778) ({\i V. rothomagensis} auct.). Perennial, the whole plant with patent hairs. Stems up to 25 cm. Leaves 1·5-3 cm, crenate, the lower suborbicular, subcordate, the upper ovate or oblong, subcordate or truncate. Stipules palmatifid; segments linear or oblong, entire, terminal slightly larger than lateral. Flowers c. 2 cm, violet, or yellowish. Spur c. 4 mm, not much longer than calycine appendages.{\i  Calcareous cliffs. • N.W. France} ({\i near Rouen}). Ga.
\par

